18/02/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- OSCE High Commissioner for Ethnic Minorities Rolf Ekeus commended the Croatian Parliament for passing a series of legislative reforms for ethnic minorities.
Ekeus met with Parliament Speaker Vladimir Sheks on Tuesday (17 February) to discuss implementation of the measures.
Sheks emphasised the success of recent elections for representatives of ethnic minorities in local governments, considered a key step in implementing the new legislation.
(HINA, HRT - 17/02/04)
